   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Fifty-six THE SATISFACTION OF MAN Scripture: John 4:14; 6:35; 7:38 Man s satisfaction is not found in material things</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Even after a man has accumulated great wealth, he is not satisfied.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Man s satisfaction is not found in psychological things</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Even after man has received honor and fame, he is still not satisfied.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Man s real satisfaction is found in his spirit</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>This satisfaction comes when God enters into man s spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Only God can satisfy the human spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Subject Two Hundred Fifty-seven THE REAL LIFE Scripture: Eph 3:19 God is man s true life</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Since God is the meaning of life and the satisfaction of man, He is the true life of a man.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>If a man is without God, not only is his an empty life, but also a false life.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The real life is one that is filled with God inwardly The real life is one that is absolutely living for God The real life is also the living out of God Himself Subject Two Hundred Fifty-eight HOW TO RECEIVE GOD</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>AND MANIFEST HIS LIFE Scripture: Acts 26:20; John 1:12-13; Rom 12:1-2 Confess that you need God Repent and turn to God Receive the Son of God as your Savior Consecrate yourself to God Practice being one spirit with the Lord</S>
